Democratic representative Brad Sherman, who is an animator of a small group in Congress, presents the problems differently, but comes to the same conclusion.
" Four hundred economic professors, including three Nobel laureates, wrote to tell us: "We ask Congress not to rush and carefully examine the path to take," he said yesterday.
